  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several key ways:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries cooperate in investigating cross-border financial crimes\n- Extradition agreements\n- Shared intelligence and evidence\n\n3. Compliance Requirements\n- Banks must implement anti-money laundering (AML) protocols\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n\n4. Standardized Legal Definitions\n- Common understanding of money laundering\n- Consistent legal approaches across jurisdictions\n- Harmonized criminal statutes\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- International sanctions\n- Asset freezing\n- Multilateral prosecution efforts\n\n6. Technological Collaboration\n- Digital tracking of financial transactions\n- Information sharing platforms\n- Coordinated cybercrime investigations\n\n7. Financial Transparency\n- Beneficial ownership registries\n- Enhanced corporate disclosure requirements\n- Cross-border financial monitoring\n\nThese intersections create a comprehensive approach to preventing and prosecuting money laundering globally.",
